<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,981,1767]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,560,1083,1109]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Distribution and ecology:—</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[560,699,1084,1110]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, Hispaniola, 
<collectingCountry box="[867,990,1084,1110]" name="Venezuela" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1009,1127,1084,1110]" name="Colombia" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1147,1246,1084,1110]" name="Ecuador" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1266,1323,1084,1110]" name="Peru" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1342,1431,1084,1110]" name="Bolivia" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, eastern and central 
<collectingCountry box="[389,466,1122,1148]" name="Brazil" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and adjacent 
<collectingCountry box="[641,756,1122,1148]" name="Paraguay" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
. Often it is common in montane pastures and savannas, especially in burnt habitats; at 
<quantity box="[520,685,1161,1187]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.125" metricValueMax="1.25" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="m" value="1125.0" valueMax="1250.0" valueMin="1000.0">1000–1250 m</quantity>
on Hispaniola, 
<quantity box="[877,1027,1161,1187]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="m" value="1900.0" valueMax="3000.0" valueMin="800.0">800–3000 m</quantity>
in the Andes, and 
<quantity box="[1254,1404,1161,1187]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.175" metricValueMax="1.65" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="m" value="1175.0" valueMax="1650.0" valueMin="700.0">700–1650 m</quantity>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,222,1200,1226]" name="Brazil" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[279,390,1200,1226]" name="Paraguay" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,981,1767]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,307,1238,1264]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nakai" authorityYear="1950" baseAuthorityName="Moric. ex Fee" box="[307,569,1239,1264]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanuginosus">
<emphasis box="[307,569,1239,1264]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Sticherus lanuginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a common species that has long been known under the name of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Copeland" authorityYear="1947" baseAuthorityName="Mart." class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="penniger">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. penniger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[548,651,1277,1303]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Copeland" authorityYear="1947" baseAuthorityName="Mart." box="[692,828,1277,1302]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="penniger">
<emphasis box="[692,828,1277,1302]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. penniger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has convinced us that this specimen represents the same species as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ching" authorityYear="1940" baseAuthorityName="Mart." box="[353,505,1316,1341]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pruinosus">
<emphasis box="[353,505,1316,1341]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. pruinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This confusion has probably arisen because pteridologists working on this species have usually seen only the photographs at 
<collectingCountry box="[810,849,1354,1380]" name="United States of America" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">US</collectingCountry>
of the type collections of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Copeland" authorityYear="1947" baseAuthorityName="Mart." box="[1196,1343,1355,1380]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="penniger">
<emphasis box="[1196,1343,1355,1380]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. penniger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These photographs show plants of a habit roughly similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nakai" authorityYear="1950" baseAuthorityName="Moric. ex Fee" box="[810,986,1393,1418]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanuginosus">
<emphasis box="[810,986,1393,1418]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. lanuginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but they do not allow a study of the diagnostic scale characters, which show that the type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Copeland" authorityYear="1947" baseAuthorityName="Mart." box="[827,962,1432,1457]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="penniger">
<emphasis box="[827,962,1432,1457]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. penniger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ching" authorityYear="1940" baseAuthorityName="Mart." box="[1103,1251,1432,1457]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pruinosus">
<emphasis box="[1103,1251,1432,1457]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. pruinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. To complicate things further, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sturm, J. W." box="[323,479,1470,1496]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="219 - 238" refId="ref34166" refString="Sturm, J. W. (1840) Gleicheniaceae, pp. 219 - 238, in: Martius, F. P. C., Eichler, G. &amp; Urban, I. (eds.), Flora Brasiliensis, Vol. I. Munchen." type="book chapter" year="1840">Sturm (1840)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Sehnem, A." box="[537,717,1470,1496]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref33729" refString="Sehnem, A. (1970) Gleicheniaceae. In Reitz R. P. (ed.) Flora Ilustrada Catarinense. Libraria Blumenauense, Brazil." type="book" year="1970">Sehnem (1970)</bibRefCitation>
adopted the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Humb. &amp; Bonpl. ex Willd." authorityName="Willd." class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Gleichenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pubescens">
<emphasis box="[939,1195,1471,1496]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Gleichenia pubescens</emphasis>
Humb. &amp; Bonpl. ex Willd.
</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nakai" authorityYear="1950" baseAuthorityName="Moric. ex Fee" box="[272,443,1509,1534]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanuginosus">
<emphasis box="[272,443,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. lanuginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName box="[579,731,1509,1534]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Gleichenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pubescens">
<emphasis box="[579,731,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">G. pubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ching" authorityYear="1940" baseAuthorityName="Willd." box="[932,1042,1509,1534]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bifidus">
<emphasis box="[932,1042,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. bifidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and has been misapplied.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,981,1767]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nakai" authorityYear="1950" baseAuthorityName="Moric. ex Fee" box="[198,456,1548,1573]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanuginosus">
<emphasis box="[198,456,1548,1573]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Sticherus lanuginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
varies considerably in size, presumably in response to habitat. Specimens from dry and sunny sites (and also perhaps from nutrient-poor soils) are smaller, with more closely held branches, and have more coriaceous segments with more strongly revolute margins. In addition, there appears to be a geographical component to the size variation, with specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[951,1071,1664,1690]" name="Venezuela" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
and southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1284,1356,1664,1690]" name="Brazil" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Brazil</collectingCountry>
being, on average, somewhat larger than those from the central Andes. This may be partly due to hybridization with other species, e.g., with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Copeland" authorityYear="1947" baseAuthorityName="Kunze" box="[434,546,1741,1766]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velatus">
<emphasis box="[434,546,1741,1766]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. velatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[584,659,1741,1767]" name="Brazil" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
